            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-24 13:26:41" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of ἄβυσσος ‘pit,’ not occurring in the NT) a location of the dead and a place where the Devil is kept ({S:06602000300012}), the abode of the beast as the antichrist ({S:06601100700026}), and of Abaddon, as the angel of the underworld ({S:06600901100016})</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>abyss</Gloss>
                <Gloss>abode of evil spirits</Gloss>
                <Gloss>very deep place</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>ἄβυσσος is sometimes rendered as ‘a very deep hole’; in other instances, ‘a hole without a bottom’ or ‘the deepest hole in the earth.’</Comments>
